    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - CAB AIR
        SUSPENSION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CAB AIR SUSPENSION</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>- For safety purposes the cab air suspension must be supplied from a pressure protected air
                        supply.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>The air suspension assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601879">Figure 79</hotlnk>) needs no lubrication and very little maintenance.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1601879" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601879" filename="../figg16/g1601879.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. Cab Air Suspension</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEIGHT CONTROL VALVE MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. HEIGHT CONTROL ALVE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BOLT, 1/4 UNC X 2</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. VALVE ARM ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. VALVE LINKAGE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. BOLT, 1/4 UNC X 2</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. HINGE ARM BRACKET (DRIVER)</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. CARRIAGE BOLT 3/8 UNC X 1</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. TOP LOCK FLANGE NUT, 3/8 UNC</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. LATCH MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. HINGE ARM</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. AIR SPRING</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. FRAME TIE TUBE</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. UNIT TOP (PASSENGER)</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. HINGE ARM BRACKET (PASSENGER)</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. SHOCK ABSORBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>17. BOLT, 7/16 UNF X 3</callout1>
                    <callout1>18. LOCK NUT, 7/16 UNF</callout1>
                    <callout1>19. JAM NUT, 3/4 UNF</callout1>
                    <callout1>20. ELBOW, 1/4 TB 1/8 M-NPT</callout1>
                    <callout1>21. SNAP RING</callout1>
                    <callout1>22. HINGE ARM BOLT, 4.250 L</callout1>
                    <callout1>23. RH FRAME MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>24. TOP LOCK NUT, 3/8 UNC</callout1>
                    <callout1>25. AIR LINE, 1/4</callout1>
                    <callout1>26. TEE, 1/4 TB 1/8 M-NPT</callout1>
                    <callout1>27. LH FRAME MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>28. AIR LINE GROMMET</callout1>
                    <callout1>29. BOLT, 7/16 UNF X 2-1/4</callout1>
                    <callout1>30. LOCK NUT, 1/4 UNC</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The following components, air lines, fittings, air springs, height control valve, shock absorbers and
                hinge arm (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601879">Items 25, 20, 26, 12, 2, 16 and 11, Figure 79</hotlnk>) should be checked at
                the time the truck is being serviced. Immediate corrective action should be taken if a serious
                malfunction occurs.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If there is an attempt to disassemble or adjust fittings on the height control valve (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601879">Item 2, Figure 79</hotlnk>), it will void the warranty. Contact the
                        air suspension manufacturer for assistance.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Periodically check the tightness of all fasteners and connections (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601879">Figure 79</hotlnk>). Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s16018_54.xml" xrefid="hl1601816">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1601816"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for proper tightening of components.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove/Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove or install the height control valve, hinge arm, air springs or shock absorbers
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601879">Items 2, 11 12 and 16, Figure 79</hotlnk>), remove mounting hardware as
                    follows.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">By looking, you can determine what mounting hardware (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601879">Items 3, 17, 18, 19, 21, 22, 24 and 29, Figure 79</hotlnk>) to remove or
                    install for the component being replaced.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If adjustment is required, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16018_52.xml" xrefid="hl1601817">ADJUSTMENTS, CAB AIR SUSPENSION
                        <xref refid="hl1601817"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
